-{"id":"beads_rust-pfx","title":"Conformance Test Harness","description":"## Overview
Implement a conformance test harness that validates br (Rust) produces identical output to bd (Go) for equivalent inputs. This ensures the Rust port is truly isomorphic to the original.

## Technical Requirements

### Test Harness Design
```rust
// tests/conformance/mod.rs

struct ConformanceTest {
    name: String,
    setup: Vec<Command>,        // Commands to set up test state
    br_command: String,         // Command to run on br
    bd_command: String,         // Equivalent command for bd
    compare: CompareMode,       // How to compare output
}

enum CompareMode {
    ExactJson,                  // JSON outputs must be identical
    NormalizedJson,             // Ignore timestamps, normalize IDs
    ContainsFields(Vec<String>), // Check specific fields match
}

fn run_conformance_test(test: &ConformanceTest) -> Result<TestResult> {
    // Create temp directories for each
    let br_dir = tempfile::tempdir()?;
    let bd_dir = tempfile::tempdir()?;

    // Initialize both
    run_cmd(&br_dir, "br init")?;
    run_cmd(&bd_dir, "bd init")?;

    // Run setup commands
    for cmd in &test.setup {
        run_cmd(&br_dir, &cmd.br_form)?;
        run_cmd(&bd_dir, &cmd.bd_form)?;
    }

    // Run test commands
    let br_output = run_cmd_capture(&br_dir, &test.br_command)?;
    let bd_output = run_cmd_capture(&bd_dir, &test.bd_command)?;

    // Compare
    match test.compare {
        CompareMode::ExactJson => {
            let br_json: Value = serde_json::from_str(&br_output)?;
            let bd_json: Value = serde_json::from_str(&bd_output)?;
            assert_eq!(br_json, bd_json);
        }
        CompareMode::NormalizedJson => {
            let br_json = normalize_json(&br_output)?;
            let bd_json = normalize_json(&bd_output)?;
            assert_eq!(br_json, bd_json);
        }
        CompareMode::ContainsFields(fields) => {
            for field in fields {
                assert_eq!(
                    extract_field(&br_output, &field)?,
                    extract_field(&bd_output, &field)?
                );
            }
        }
    }

    Ok(TestResult::Pass)
}
```

### Test Categories

#### 1. Create Command Tests
```rust
conformance_test! {
    name: "create_basic",
    setup: [],
    br_command: "br create 'Test issue' --type=bug --priority=1 --json",
    bd_command: "bd create 'Test issue' --type=bug --priority=1 --json",
    compare: ContainsFields(vec!["title", "type", "priority", "status"]),
}
```

#### 2. List/Query Tests
```rust
conformance_test! {
    name: "list_by_status",
    setup: [
        "create 'Open issue'",
        "create 'Closed issue'",
        "close <id2>",
    ],
    br_command: "br list --status=open --json",
    bd_command: "bd list --status=open --json",
    compare: NormalizedJson,
}
```

#### 3. Dependency Tests
```rust
conformance_test! {
    name: "dep_blocking",
    setup: [
        "create 'Blocker'",
        "create 'Blocked'",
        "dep add <id2> <id1>",
    ],
    br_command: "br blocked --json",
    bd_command: "bd blocked --json",
    compare: ContainsFields(vec!["blocked_by"]),
}
```

#### 4. Sync Tests
```rust
conformance_test! {
    name: "sync_roundtrip",
    setup: [
        "create 'Issue 1'",
        "create 'Issue 2'",
        "dep add <id2> <id1>",
    ],
    test_sequence: [
        // Export from br
        ("br sync --flush-only", None),
        // Import to bd
        ("bd sync --import-only", None),
        // Verify bd sees same data
        ("bd list --json", "br list --json"),
    ],
    compare: NormalizedJson,
}
```

### Running Conformance Tests
```bash
# Run all conformance tests
cargo test conformance

# Run specific test
cargo test conformance::create_basic

# Run with verbose output
cargo test conformance -- --nocapture
```

